cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a data augmentation protocol for sequence models, which is relevant to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions reducing error rates and perplexity, which are common evaluation metrics in neural networks, suggesting relevance to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions a semantic parsing task, which suggests relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
